<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

    <PropertyGroup>
        <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>
        <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
        <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
        <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>

        <!--
        AOT smoke test #2 (wolverine#2746 sub-PR I, companion to
        Wolverine.AotSmoke). Validates the AOT-clean runtime path:
        pre-generate handler code via the codegen-write CLI,
        commit the output under Internal/Generated/WolverineHandlers/,
        boot under TypeLoadMode.Static + AssertAllPreGeneratedTypesExist
        = true, dispatch a message, verify the static-loaded handler
        fired. If a regression breaks the static-load contract, this
        build/run fails in CI rather than downstream consumers'.

        Two failure modes this smoke catches:

        1. Pre-generated handler missing or stale.
           AssertAllPreGeneratedTypesExist=true makes the host throw
           at Compile time if the StaticTypeLoader cannot locate the
           expected MessageHandler subclass in this assembly. This pins
           down regressions in the codegen output format or the type-name
           hashing scheme.

        2. Runtime regenerates code under Static mode.
           The host registers a sentinel IAssemblyGenerator that throws
           on use. Any silent fallback to Roslyn compilation under
           TypeLoadMode.Static fails the smoke immediately with a clear
           "static-mode boot triggered runtime compilation" stack.

        Refresh procedure when the codegen output format changes:
        run the AotSmoke.Static project with the codegen-write CLI args,
        then commit the regenerated files under Internal/Generated/.

        IsAotCompatible=true is intentionally not set on this project.
        The goal here is to validate the static-load contract end-to-end
        (which currently still requires Wolverine surfaces that are not
        AOT-clean to BOOT, even though the dispatch path is). The
        sister Wolverine.AotSmoke project covers the IsAotCompatible=true
        analyzer story for the value-shape surface.
        -->
    </PropertyGroup>

    <ItemGroup>
        <ProjectReference Include="..\..\Wolverine\Wolverine.csproj" />
    </ItemGroup>

</Project>
